The paper discusses reinforcement learning algorithms and their application to control tasks, which are typically studied in the machine learning subfield of control theory. The paper also discusses the use of artificial neural networks as function approximators, which is a common technique in the subfield of deep learning. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). The paper also discusses the role of the basal ganglia and midbrain dopamine system in reinforcement learning, which falls under the subfield of systems and control (cs.SY). Finally, the paper discusses the use of sparse distributed representations, which is a technique commonly used in computer vision (cs.CV).
